Actions.Text: AMEND AND RECOMMIT TO ELECTION LAW
REFERENCE CHANGED TO WAYS AND MEANS

Title: Permits political parties to perform certain functions without forming county committees
Summary: Permits political parties to designate or nominate candidates for positions to be filled by all the voters, and perform other functions without forming county committees.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the election law, in relation to permit political parties to perform certain functions without forming county committees
